 #!Rtall320 Resetting the Camera #!N #!N #!N To return the image 
to a "front" view that includes the entire object, select the 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Reset #!EF option of the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   View Control... #!EF dialog 
box, or use the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Ctrl+F #!EF accelerator key. #!N #!N 
You can also use this option if you bring in a 
new data set and want to create a new camera appropriate 
for the data. Note: You can also reset the camera by 
using the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   resetCamera #!EF parameter to the Image tool (see 
Image in IBM Visualization Data Explorer User's Reference). #!N #!N #!N 
